  45- * The RateLimiter implementation can be set via the <code>rateLimitClassName</code> init param. The default
  46- * implementation, <code>org.apache.catalina.util.FastRateLimiter</code>, is optimized for efficiency and low overhead
  47- * so it converts some configured values to more efficient values. For example, a configuration of a 60 seconds time
  48: * bucket is converted to 65.536 seconds. That allows for very fast bucket calculation using bit shift arithmetic. In
  49- * order to remain true to the user intent, the configured number of requests is then multiplied by the same ratio, so a
  50- * configuration of 100 Requests per 60 seconds, has the real values of 109 Requests per 65 seconds. An alternative
  51- * implementation, <code>org.apache.catalina.util.ExactRateLimiter</code>, is intended to provide a less efficient but
